<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I work across Brisbane's outer southern corridor and understand who buys in Heathwood. The core buyer is practical: a first home buyer or young family who has compared Algester and Forest Lake, found the price points tighter than expected, and arrived in Heathwood with a budget that goes further. These buyers move decisively when a property is correctly priced and clearly presented. Understanding that buyer profile is the starting point for every campaign I run here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Heathwood's strongest residential pockets sit closest to Forest Lake, where the housing stock is more consistent and the neighbourhood feel more purely residential. The suburb's mixed-use zoning means there is genuine variation in what borders a residential property, and sellers who understand how buyers read that variation can position their campaign to draw the right buyer pool rather than the wrong one. The motorway interchange at Heathwood is one of the most important commuter nodes in the outer southern corridor, and buyers who need efficient access to both the Ipswich and Logan motorway systems specifically target this pocket.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Outer Southern Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Brisbane's southern corridor</p>
